Done. F-005 is fixed. Root cause: `AgentExecutor` returns empty `output` for statement-type messages (like "quick heads up: i'm vegetarian") when the LLM fires tool calls (`remember_about_user`) but emits no final text response. Fix is two-layer: (1) `lc_agent.py` — retry with a plain ack LLM call if output is empty; (2) `api/chat.py` — last-resort `>= 40 char` fallback if the ack call also fails. Next iteration should tackle F-006 (concurrency-empty-reply, same class).
